page.title: 09GROVE LAKE
page.content: GROVE LAKE Grove Lake is more usually called The Duckpond by the locals.The site was purchased and developed as a public amenity about 1971. Tiptree has a big duck pond.It stands at the beginning of the main street.It has moorhens, mallards and other water birds.The main road runs beside the duck pond.The pond has railings round it.In the middle there is an island with trees and flowers.The ducks sleep on this island.The village people look after the ducks by feeding them bread but the owners feed the ducks properly.The pond is man made.
